---
layout: article
title: Databases
description: "Structured application data in Appwrite projects: databases and tables with typed attributes and indexes, row-level permissions aligned with Authentication (`user`, `team`, `role`, `public`), queries and ordering, relationships and geo queries, plus transactions, pagination, bulk and CSV tools, backups, and type generation for production teams."
back: /docs
---

Appwrite Databases is the managed tables layer for structured records: schema definition, row lifecycle, and the APIs clients and backends use to read and write data consistently.

You organize work into databases and tables, then define attributes, indexes, and constraints that match your domain. The model maps cleanly to common product data (profiles, orders, content, inventory) without exposing a shared database password to every client.

[Permissions](/docs/products/databases/permissions) are evaluated per row and can reference the same identities and membership you manage in [Authentication](/docs/products/auth): `user`, `team`, `role`, and `public` scopes, including team-scoped multi-tenant patterns. [Labels](/docs/products/auth/labels) from Authentication can participate in rules when you need coarse tiers or entitlements without hard-coding user identifiers in application code.

For reads and navigation you use [queries](/docs/products/databases/queries) and [order](/docs/products/databases/order) for lists and search, [relationships](/docs/products/databases/relationships) when data spans tables, and [geo queries](/docs/products/databases/geo-queries) for maps or "near me" behavior. For writes and data movement at volume you add [transactions](/docs/products/databases/transactions), [pagination](/docs/products/databases/pagination), [bulk operations](/docs/products/databases/bulk-operations), [CSV imports](/docs/products/databases/csv-imports) and [CSV exports](/docs/products/databases/csv-exports), [backups](/docs/products/databases/backups), and [type generation](/docs/products/databases/type-generation). Where it fits your stack, [offline sync](/docs/products/databases/offline) and [AI suggestions](/docs/products/databases/ai-suggestions) extend the same surface.

{% info title="Looking for file storage?" %}
Databases hold structured rows. For images, PDFs, or video, use [Appwrite Storage](/docs/products/storage).
{% /info %}

