# Security and permissions {% #security-and-permissions %}

Access control is defined at the row: who may create, read, update, or delete each record, and how team membership or roles participate in those checks. Console configuration, API keys, and client session context all affect what a given call is allowed to do.

[Databases permissions](/docs/products/databases/permissions) is the product reference for scopes, rule composition, and common multi-tenant layouts. [Authentication security](/docs/products/auth/security) and [Security](/docs/advanced/security) cover identity hardening, transport and encryption posture, audit logging, and broader platform guarantees. [Platform permissions](/docs/advanced/platform/permissions) documents project-level roles for Console and API access separate from end-user row rules.

# Operations at scale {% #operations-at-scale %}

These guides focus on predictable list behavior, coordinated writes, and moving large batches without surprises.

Use [pagination](/docs/products/databases/pagination) and [order](/docs/products/databases/order) for feeds and admin tables. Use [transactions](/docs/products/databases/transactions) when several writes must succeed or fail together, and [atomic numeric operations](/docs/products/databases/atomic-numeric-operations) for counters under concurrent updates. Import or export big batches with [CSV imports](/docs/products/databases/csv-imports) and [CSV exports](/docs/products/databases/csv-exports). On the client, combine [type generation](/docs/products/databases/type-generation) with [offline sync](/docs/products/databases/offline) when typed models or disconnected use matter, and [AI suggestions](/docs/products/databases/ai-suggestions) where supported to accelerate schema work.
